title: A Treatise Of Human Nature, Volume 2
creator: David Hume
description: LibriVox recording of A Treatise Of Human Nature, Volume 2, by David Hume. Read by George Yeager This book, published in two volumes called "books" by the author, is a treatment of everything from the origin of our ideas to how they are to be divided. It includes important statements of Scepticism and Hume's experimental method. Part 1 deals with the nature of ideas. Part 2 deals with the ideas of space and time. Part 3 deals with knowledge and probability. Part 4 deals with skeptical and other systems of philosophy, including a discussion of the soul and personal identity. (Summary by Wikipedia) This volume contains Books 2 and 3. Volume 1 (or Book 1) is also available as a Librivox audiobook For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
